
[1]comfortable

   COMFORTABLE, a.

   1. Being in a state of ease, or moderate enjoyment; as a person after
   sickness or pain. This is the most common use of the word in the U.
   States.

   2. Admitting comfort; that may afford comfort.

   Who can promise him a comfortable appearance before his dreadful judge?

   3. Giving comfort; affording consolation.

   The word of my lord the king shall now be comfortable. 2 Sam. 14.

   4. Placing above want and affording moderate enjoyment; as a
   comfortable provision for old age.
